BASE64 NEWS -- History of user-visible changes.
Copyright (C) 2004, 2005 Simon Josefsson
See the end for copying conditions.

* Version 1.3 (released 2005-06-24)

** License were updated to reflect new FSF address.

* Version 1.2 (released 2005-01-04)

** A man page for the tool has been added.

** The data to convert can now be taken from command line argument.
As in `base64 foo'.

** The tool now print a banner at startup, that can be disabled via --quiet.
When built on a system that has isatty(3) (e.g., any POSIX platform)
it will also be disabled when the standard output is not a TTY.

** The help text for -w and --wrap has been improved.
This is to clarify that -w do not take an optional parameter.

** Swedish translation added.

** More self tests.

* Version 1.1 (released 2004-12-28)

** The -w and --wrap parameters should now work properly.

* Version 1.0 (released 2004-12-28)

** Initial release.

